defs.docs:
This library provides implementations of `Mutex`, `RwLock`, `Condvar` and
 `Once` that are smaller, faster and more flexible than those in the Rust
 standard library. It also provides a `ReentrantMutex` type.

defs.name: WaitTimeoutResult
defs.docs:
A type indicating whether a timed wait on a condition variable returned
 due to a time out or not.

defs.name: timed_out
defs.docs: Returns whether the wait was known to have timed out.

defs.name: Condvar
defs.docs: A Condition Variable

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a new condition variable which is ready to be waited on and
 notified.

defs.name: notify_one
defs.docs: Wakes up one blocked thread on this condvar.

defs.name: notify_all
defs.docs: Wakes up all blocked threads on this condvar.

defs.name: wait
defs.docs:
Blocks the current thread until this condition variable receives a
 notification.

defs.name: wait_until
defs.value: fn <T> (&self, mutex_guard: &mut MutexGuard<'_, T>, timeout: Instant) -> WaitTimeoutResult
defs.docs:
Waits on this condition variable for a notification, timing out after
 the specified time instant.

defs.name: wait_for
defs.value: fn <T> (&self, mutex_guard: &mut MutexGuard<'_, T>, timeout: Duration) -> WaitTimeoutResult
defs.docs:
Waits on this condition variable for a notification, timing out after a
 specified duration.

defs.name: Mutex
defs.docs: A mutual exclusion primitive useful for protecting shared data

defs.name: MutexGuard
defs.docs:
An RAII implementation of a "scoped lock" of a mutex. When this structure is
 dropped (falls out of scope), the lock will be unlocked.

defs.name: MappedMutexGuard
defs.docs:
An RAII mutex guard returned by `MutexGuard::map`, which can point to a
 subfield of the protected data.

defs.name: New
defs.docs: A closure has not been executed yet

defs.name: Poisoned
defs.docs: A closure was executed but panicked.

defs.name: InProgress
defs.docs: A thread is currently executing a closure.

defs.name: Done
defs.docs: A closure has completed successfully.

defs.name: OnceState
defs.docs: Current state of a `Once`.

defs.name: poisoned
defs.docs: Returns whether the associated `Once` has been poisoned.

defs.name: done
defs.docs:
Returns whether the associated `Once` has successfully executed a
 closure.

defs.name: Once
defs.docs:
A synchronization primitive which can be used to run a one-time
 initialization. Useful for one-time initialization for globals, FFI or
 related functionality.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Once` value.

defs.name: state
defs.docs: Returns the current state of this `Once`.

defs.name: call_once
defs.docs:
Performs an initialization routine once and only once. The given closure
 will be executed if this is the first time `call_once` has been called,
 and otherwise the routine will *not* be invoked.

defs.name: call_once_force
defs.docs: Performs the same function as `call_once` except ignores poisoning.

defs.name: RawMutex
defs.docs: Raw mutex type backed by the parking lot.

defs.name: RawRwLock
defs.docs: Raw reader-writer lock type backed by the parking lot.

defs.name: RawThreadId
defs.docs: Implementation of the `GetThreadId` trait for `lock_api::ReentrantMutex`.

defs.name: ReentrantMutex
defs.docs: A mutex which can be recursively locked by a single thread.

defs.name: ReentrantMutexGuard
defs.docs:
An RAII implementation of a "scoped lock" of a reentrant mutex. When this structure
 is dropped (falls out of scope), the lock will be unlocked.

defs.name: MappedReentrantMutexGuard
defs.docs:
An RAII mutex guard returned by `ReentrantMutexGuard::map`, which can point to a
 subfield of the protected data.

defs.name: RwLock
defs.docs: A reader-writer lock

defs.name: RwLockReadGuard
defs.docs:
RAII structure used to release the shared read access of a lock when
 dropped.

defs.name: RwLockWriteGuard
defs.docs:
RAII structure used to release the exclusive write access of a lock when
 dropped.

defs.name: MappedRwLockReadGuard
defs.docs:
An RAII read lock guard returned by `RwLockReadGuard::map`, which can point to a
 subfield of the protected data.

defs.name: MappedRwLockWriteGuard
defs.docs:
An RAII write lock guard returned by `RwLockWriteGuard::map`, which can point to a
 subfield of the protected data.

defs.name: RwLockUpgradableReadGuard
defs.docs:
RAII structure used to release the upgradable read access of a lock when
 dropped.
